[[Image:The Mt Sawa is looked at from Hikone Castle Shiga.jpg|thumb|Mt Sawa seen from Hikone Castle]]
{{nihongo|'''Sawayama Castle'''|佐和山城|Sawayama-jō}} was a castle in the city of [[Hikone, Shiga|Hikone]], [[Shiga Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. 

This castle was an important military stronghold of [[Ōmi Province]]. The [[Azai clan]] held this castle in the [[Sengoku Period]]. [[Ishida Mitsunari]] held it at the end of the 16th century after the ruin of the Azai clan. This castle was attacked by [[Kobayakawa Hideaki]] after the [[Battle of Sekigahara]]. The castle surrendered at half a day though the brother of Mitsunari, [[Ishida Masazumi]], defended it.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite book |title= Sekigahara 1600 - The final struggle for power|last= Bryant|first= Anthony J|authorlink= |coauthors= |year= 2003|publisher= Osprey Publishing|location= |isbn= 1-85532-395-8|pages= 17, 79}}&lt;/ref&gt;  Afterwards, [[Ii Naomasa]] occupied Sawayama Castle. However, he destroyed it, and moved to [[Hikone Castle]].

